Fix the map interactivity - buildings are not clickable. Make the following changes:

PROBLEM: Map and buildings are not responding to clicks.

SOLUTION - Make buildings fully interactive:

1. ADD BUILDING CLICK HANDLERS:
   - When map loads and user searches a location, generate 25-30 clickable building markers
   - Each building should be a Mapbox Marker or a clickable map layer
   - Buildings must have onClick event handlers attached

2. BUILDING GENERATION:
   When location is selected (after search):
```javascript
   // Generate buildings near the searched coordinates
   const buildings = [];
   for (let i = 0; i < 25; i++) {
     const building = {
       id: `building_${i}`,
       coordinates: {
         lat: searchedLat + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.01, // Random offset
         lon: searchedLon + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 0.01
       },
       height: Math.random() * 80 + 20, // 20-100m height
       interventions: [],
       color: '#64748b' // Default gray
     };
     buildings.push(building);
   }
```

3. RENDER BUILDINGS AS CLICKABLE ELEMENTS:
   
   Option A - Using Mapbox Markers (EASIEST):
```javascript
   buildings.forEach(building => {
     const el = document.createElement('div');
     el.className = 'building-marker';
     el.style.backgroundColor = building.color;
     el.style.width = '20px';
     el.style.height = '20px';
     el.style.borderRadius = '4px';
     el.style.cursor = 'pointer';
     el.style.border = '2px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3)';
     
     el.addEventListener('click', () => handleBuildingClick(building.id));
     
     new mapboxgl.Marker(el)
       .setLngLat([building.coordinates.lon, building.coordinates.lat])
       .addTo(map);
   });
```
   
   Option B - Using Mapbox 3D Fill-Extrusion Layer (MORE IMPRESSIVE):
```javascript
   map.addLayer({
     id: 'buildings-3d',
     type: 'fill-extrusion',
     source: {
       type: 'geojson',
       data: {
         type: 'FeatureCollection',
         features: buildings.map(b => ({
           type: 'Feature',
           properties: {
             id: b.id,
             height: b.height,
             color: b.color
           },
           geometry: {
             type: 'Polygon',
             coordinates: [[
               [b.coordinates.lon - 0.0001, b.coordinates.lat - 0.0001],
               [b.coordinates.lon + 0.0001, b.coordinates.lat - 0.0001],
               [b.coordinates.lon + 0.0001, b.coordinates.lat + 0.0001],
               [b.coordinates.lon - 0.0001, b.coordinates.lat + 0.0001],
               [b.coordinates.lon - 0.0001, b.coordinates.lat - 0.0001]
             ]]
